snippet.textDisplay: It's really interesting. The "perks" of being a man described in this song that are being sought after are either 1. non-exclusive to being a man or 2. negative things. Being an uncool, poor leader who is constantly questioned and judged is not a woman-only issue. Maybe all men in Hollywood or the music industry are "perfect", but it's definitely not an accurate representation of the world (or at least the part of the world I know). And the things like sleeping around, flexing your dollars and being rude to people... the people who approve/encourage those things are NOT people you should be seeking approval from. Maybe men "in the industry" are disproportionally allowed to act this way and it's seen as okay... but that doesn't mean it's okay. It just means people don't know what success really is. Selflessness and loving others will make you happy; not fame, approval or being a man.
